      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "While it might seem convenient, self-medicating with an extra puff of your salbutamol without medical advice can lead to potential complications, like medication overuse or an incorrect dosage, which can worsen your condition over time. It's important to follow a treatment plan as prescribed by your healthcare provider. If you're experiencing persistent symptoms like wheezing, it's better to err on the side of caution and make a doctor's appointment. They can assess your situation and adjust your treatment accordingly, ensuring your safety and health.",
      "source": "target",
